^Help - Pemote
USAGE: .pemote ^user message
WHERE: ^user^ is a user (currently online) you wish to send an emote to.
       ^message^ is what you wish to emote to ^user^.

Use this command when you want to send a private emote to another user.
Nobody but the other ^user^ will see the ^message^ you send.

EXAMPLES
  .pemote bob smiles.

SEE ALSO
  ^.help tell^, ^.help emote^, ^.help semote^, ^.help abbr
